    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-8">
        <!-- Page Header -->
        <div class="mb-8">
            <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-2">Privacy Policy</h1>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">Last Updated: November 18, 2025</p>
        </div>

        <!-- Opening Paragraph -->
        <div class="prose dark:prose-invert max-w-none mb-8">
            <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
                At GPRA (Guitar Practice Routine App), we take your privacy seriously. This policy explains what data we collect,
                how we use it, and what rights you have over your information. We believe in transparency, so we've written this
                in plain English (well, as plain as privacy policies get). ðŸŽ¸
            </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Core Privacy Statement -->
        <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-lg shadow-md p-6 mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-4">What We Collect</h2>
            <div class="space-y-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
                <p>
                    <strong>Practice Data:</strong> The items, routines, chord charts, and practice events you create while using GPRA.
                    This is your data - you own it, we just store it for you.
                </p>
                <p>
                    <strong>Account Information:</strong> Your email address, username, and if you signed up with Google or Tidal,
                    your encrypted OAuth ID from those services.
                </p>
                <p>
                    <strong>Subscription Data:</strong> If you're on a paid tier, we store your Stripe customer ID, subscription tier,
                    and payment history. Stripe handles all the actual payment processing - we never see your credit card numbers.
                </p>
                <p>
                    <strong>Optional Stuff:</strong> If you add your own Anthropic API key (the "byoClaude" feature), we encrypt it
                    and store it for you. You can remove it anytime.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-lg shadow-md p-6 mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-4">How We Use It</h2>
            <div class="space-y-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
                <p>
                    We use your data to provide GPRA's practice tracking services. That's it. We're not in the business of selling your
                    information, and we never will be.
                </p>
                <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
                    <li>Process payments via Stripe (they're PCI compliant, so your payment info is secure)</li>
                    <li>Send password reset emails via Mailgun when you forget your password</li>
                    <li>Show you ads on the free tier (via Google AdSense) - this helps us keep the free tier free!</li>
                    <li>Improve the app with analytics (PostHog) - you can opt out anytime in Account Settings</li>
                </ul>
                <p class="font-semibold mt-4">
                    Your data will <span class="text-orange-600 dark:text-orange-400">NEVER</span> be sold to, shared with, or otherwise
                    divulged to third parties. Ever. Period. Nothing personal. (Pun intended.)
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-lg shadow-md p-6 mb-8">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-4">Your Rights (GDPR & CPRA)</h2>
            <div class="space-y-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
                <p>
                    You have complete control over your data:
                </p>
                <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
                    <li><strong>Download your data:</strong> Export your practice history (last 90 days) as CSV or JSON anytime from Account Settings</li>
                    <li><strong>Delete your account:</strong> Remove all your data permanently. You can schedule deletion for your next renewal date (with a prorated refund) or delete immediately. See Account Settings.</li>
                    <li><strong>Opt out of analytics:</strong> Toggle off PostHog tracking in Account Settings</li>
                    <li><strong>Update your information:</strong> Change your email, username, or API key anytime</li>
                </ul>
                <p class="mt-4">
                    Questions about your data? Email us at <a href="mailto:support@guitarpracticeroutine.com"
                    class="text-orange-600 dark:text-orange-400 hover:underline">support@guitarpracticeroutine.com</a>
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Third-Party Services -->
